tt iii is an independent qualified “financial expert” who has developed his knowledge through  years of experience at kpmg over  years as a partner his active board participation has continued to refine it further he serves on the audit and the human resource committees of brooks automation was past chair of its special committee and served on its finance committee he is a director of the y of martha’s vineyard chair of its governance and cochair of its strategic planning committees board governor and treasurer of the edgartown golf club director and treasurer of the william h hart realty trust inc president and treasurer of the hart haven community association treasurer of massachusetts society of genealogists  mvi chapter auditor pro bono for st andrew’s episcopal church of edgartown and trinity episcopal church of oak bluffs past director of helix technology and past director of greencore us holdings he currently holds american college of corporate directors highest professional director certification an executive mastershis writing career since retiring in  al’s dabbling in family history has grown to a minor obsession and evolved into a second career he has published several articles in a genealogical publication made presentations on the subject instructed courses for the adult continuing education of martha’s vineyard and in  published his first book the immigrant one from my four legged stool for more on als avocation visit his website wwwmyfourleggedstoolcom als second career along with doing crossword puzzles and reading financial publications keeps his mind sharp while golf tennis hockey and maintaining his many gardens in the summer keeps his body activeal and his wife jill reside in oak bluffs have four children and eight grandchildrenexperiencetreasurer  mvi chaptermassachusetts society of genealogists incnovember  – present  years  monthsdirectorymca – present  yearstreasurer board of governorsedgartown golf clubaugust  – present  yearsmembermassachus